  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Vers l&apos;optimisation du business du riz</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Achat de 2 balances plate-forme&#xC9;coles champs paysan et pratique de la Gestion Int&#xE9;gr&#xE9;e de la Fertilit&#xE9; des Sols (GIFS)S&#xE9;ances d&apos;information des membres du contrat riz et campagnes de mobilisation des non-membres &#xE0; rejoindre la coop&#xE9;rative.R&#xE9;viser le MAPAF (manuel de proc&#xE9;dures administratives et financi&#xE8;res)Achat d&apos;un modem pour acc&#xE8;s internet  frais mensuel de communication et papeterie bureauAtelier pour le d&#xE9;veloppement d&apos;un plan strat&#xE9;gique (plan financier inclus)Atelier pour le d&#xE9;veloppement d&apos;un plan d&apos;affaire (+plan de tr&#xE9;sorerie et plan des op&#xE9;rations)Am&#xE9;lioration de la comptabilit&#xE9; en Excel et pr&#xE9;paration des &#xE9;tats financiersSuivi du contrat et des livraisons &#xE0; BralimaSensibiliser les jeunes &#xE0; int&#xE9;grer les organes de la coop&#xE9;rationOrganiser les rencontres entre les membres des organes (CA  CS et AG)Organisation d&apos;une journ&#xE9;e porte ouverte</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Created in 2003  the Cooperative of actions for the development of peasant farmers (ADPA) has long functioned as a non-profit organization awaiting the support (subsidies) of the various partners and international non-governmental organizations which flew to the aid of the Congolese populations in situation of advanced vulnerability. But since 2016  ADPA has turned to Agri-business  specializing in the Rice sector.
ADPA started delivering rice to Bralima Bukavu since 2017 with many difficulties because it was not organized at all and it was not until 2020 that ADPA integrated the second phase of the 20at-8529 rice project. Like the other 5 cooperatives  ADPA first went through the normal process to be one of Agriterra&apos;s client. ADPA must receive training on financial management  Mycoop 1 2 3 and 4 training  governance so that it can do its business well. For this year 2020 and with the support of AGRITERRA  ADPA will deliver 500 tonnes of white rice to Bralima.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The cooperative would like to  professionalize in the activity of collecting and selling rice of its members  in order to make it more profitable. So  they can earn more income and sell large quantities of quality rice to the Bralima.</narrative>
  </description>
